France's President Emmanuel Macron has tested positive for Coronavirus, his office says. Macron  took a test after developing symptoms and will now isolate himself for seven days, the Elysée Palace said in a statement. "In accordance with current health regulations applicable to all, the President of the Republic will isolate himself for 7 days. He continues to work and carry out his activities remotely." There have been two million confirmed cases in the country since the epidemic began, with more than 59,400 deaths, according to data from Johns Hopkins University. 